会议中未解决的问题

Q1 正则图补图的特征多项式?

A1 设G为度为k的正则图, 顶点数为n. 由于G―度为n−k, 故λ1(G―)=n−k, 相应的特征向量为1. 若λixi=A(G)xi, 则

(J−I−A)x1=11Txi−(λi+1)xi=−(λi+1)xi.

故PG―(x)=PG(−x−1)⋅(−1)n(x−n+k+1)x+k+1.

将结论用于join graph, 则

PG1▽G2(x)=PG1(x)PG2(x)(x−k1)(x−k2)[(x−k1)(x−k2)−n1n2].

Q2 称G为Cartesian product可分解的, 若且仅若存在非平凡图G1,G2使得G1◻G2=G. 试寻找例子以说明Cartesian product可分解的图不一定存在唯一的最小分解.

A2 等价于说明非负整系数多项式环非UFD. 注意到

(x3+1)(x2+x+1)=(x+1)(x4+x2+1).

对图G​, 定义G1=G, Gn=G◻Gn−1, 则

(G3∪˙K1)◻(G2∪˙G∪˙K1)=(G∪˙K1)◻(G4∪˙G2∪˙K1).

不妨取G=P2=Q1为1维超立方体, 下证明(G3∪˙K1)非Cartesian product可分解: 注意到(G3∪˙K1)顶点数为9且不连通, 显然无法成为两个不连通3-顶点图之Cartesian product. 同理, (G2∪˙G∪˙K1)之顶点数为质数, 显然不可Cartesian product分解.

Q3 给定A(G)与A(G−j)的谱(邻接矩阵未知), 试计算A(G)中特征值λj对应的特征向量xj中第k项分量之模长, 即xkj. 此处需假定A(G)之谱无重根.

A3 注意到PG−j(x)为adj(xI−A)的j,j项余子式, 设1j为第j项为1而其余项为0的向量, 则

PG−j(x)=(1j)Tadj(xI−A)1j=PG(x)(1j)T(xI−A)−11j=PG(x)(1j)T(∑i1x−λiPi)1j=PG(x)eiT(∑iEix−λi)ei=PG(x)∑iαij2x−λi

代入x=λk​, 则

PG−j(λk)=αjk2∏i≠k(λk−λi).

此处

|xkj|2=αjk2=∏i≠k(λk−λj)∏μ∈Spec(G−j)(λk−μ).

Angle Matrix of a Graph

αij, the angle

For any simple graph G(V,E) with neither directions, multiple edges, loops G(V,E), the adjacency matrix A=A(G) is symmetric. In light of the polar decomposition, we have

A=QTΛQ=∑i=1rλi⋅Pi=∑i=1rλi⋅QTEiQ

where λ1>λ2>⋯>λr, On(R)∋Q=(x1,x2,…,xn).

  • αij:∥Eixj∥=xjTEixj denotes the ij-th angle, that is, the i-th index of eigenvector xj. The angle matrix is given by (αij)r×n.
  • ∑i=1rαij2=∑ixjTEixj=xjTIxj=1.
  • ∑j=1nαij2=∑jxjTEixj=trace(QTEiQ)=dim⁡Eλi. Here Eλi denotes the root space of λi.
βi, the main angle

The main angle βi is defined as ∥Pi⋅1n∥n. Hence

∑iβi2=1TI1n=1.

For any polynomial P(x) which is well-defined on the ring R and matrix ring M(n,R), we notice that PiPj=O for any i≠j. Hence we deduce that

P(A)=∑iP(λi)Pi

with the corollary

1TP(A)1=n∑iP(λi)βi2.

Further more, the polynomial P can be replaced by some function once its convergence is determined.

Operation, Modification&Compositions of Graphs

Basic Graph Operations

Simple operations:

  • The disjoint union G1∪˙G2.
  • The complement G―.
  • The join G1▽G2:=G1―∪˙G2――.
  • The vertex-deleted graph G−j.
  • The pendant-added graph Gj.
  • The coalescence Gu⋅Hv, or G⋅H for short, w.r.t. u∈V(G), v∈V(H).
  • The bridged graph GuvH.

Some special operations:

  • The corona G∘H.
  • The subdivision graph S(G).
  • The line graph L(G).

NEPS(non-complete extended p-sum) operations.

Characteristic Polynomials under the Modifications

For disjoint union, we have

PG1∪˙G2(x)=PG1(x)PG2(x).

Further more, for any finite graph set {Gi}i=1m we have

P∪˙{Gi}i=1m(x)=∏i=1mPGi(x).

For complement, we have

PG―(x)=det(xI−J+I+A)=det((x+1)I+A)−1Tadj((x+1)I+A)1=(−1)nPG(−x−1)(1−1T((x+1)I+A)−11)=(−1)nPG(−x−1)(1−n∑i=1rβi2x+1+λi)

Lemma (UNNECESSARY). det(A+uvT)=det(A)+vTadj(A)u.

Proof of the lemma. Since

|1vT0A+uvT|=|1vT−uA|=|1+vTA−1uvT0A|

Q.E.D.

For join, we have

PG1∪˙G2―(x)=(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)(1−(n1+n2)∑i=1sβi2x+1+λi)(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)(1−n1∑i=1s(βi(1))2x+1+λi−n2∑i=1s(βi(2))2x+1+λi)=−(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)+(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)(1−n1∑i=1s(βi(1))2x+1+λi)+(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)(1−n2∑i=1s(βi(2))2x+1+λi)=(−1)n2PG1―(x)PG2(−x−1)+(−1)n1PG2―(x)PG1(−x−1)−(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1).

Hence

PG1▽G2(x)+(−1)n1+n2PG1∪˙G2(−x−1)=(−1)n2PG1―(x)PG2(−x−1)+(−1)n1PG2―(x)PG1(−x−1).

We deduce that

PG1▽G2(x)=PG1(x)PG2(x)(1−n1n2∑i=1r1∑j=1r2(βi(1)βj(2))2(x−λi(1))(x−λj(2))).
Characteristic Polynomials under the Compositions

For vertex-deleted graph G−j, PG−j(x) is the j-th diagonal element of adj(xI−A). Since

adj(xI−A)=PG(x)(xI−A)−1=PG(x)∑i=1rPix−λi

we deduce that PG−j(x)=PG(x)∑i=1rαij2x−λi.

For the pendant-added graph Gj, we notice that

PGj(x)=xPG(x)−PG−j(x).

Hence PGj(x)=PG(x)(x−∑i=1rαij2x−λi).

For coalescence G⋅H in which u∈G and v∈H, we have

PG⋅H(x)=|xI−A′−rO−rTx−sTO−sxI−B′|=|xI−A′−rO−rTx−sTO0xI−B′|+|xI−A′0O−rTx−sTO−sxI−B′|−|xI−A′0O−rTx−sTO0xI−B′|=PG(x)PH−v(x)+PG−u(x)PH(x)−xPG−u(x)PH−v(x).

For the bridged graph GuvH, we have

PGuvH(x)=PGu(x)PH−v(x)+PG(x)PH(x)−xPG(x)PH−v(x)=PG(x)PH(x)−PG−u(x)PH−v(x)

For corona graph G∘H, we have

PG∘H(x)=det|xI−A−J1−J2⋯−Jn−J1TxI−B−J2TxI−B⋮⋱−JnTxI−B|=det|xI−A−mx−rI−J1−J2⋯−Jn0xI−B0xI−B⋮⋱0xI−B|=PG(x−mx−r)(PH(x))n

where n=|V(G)|.

For subdivision graph, we can notice that A(S(G))=(OBTBO). Here B denotes the induced graph (from edges to vertices). Hence

PS(G)(x)=x|E|−|V|QG(x2)

where QG(x) denotes the characteristic polynomial of signless Laplacian BBT=A+D.

For line graph L(G), the characteristic polynomial is given by

PL(G)(x)=(x+2)|E|−|V|(x)QG(x+2).
NEPS(non-complete extended p-sum)

The NEPS is a multiple operation of a set of graph via a given tuple B⊂{0,1}n∖{0}n, e.g. {Gi}i=1n. It outcomes NEPS({Gi}i=1n,B) satisfying:

  • The vertices of the the outcome is the (classical) Cartesian product

    ∏i=1nV(Gi)=G1×⋯×Gn.

  • The vertices (x1,…,xn) and (y1,…,yn) are adjacent if and only if there exists a β⊂B such that βi=0⇔xi=yi and xj∼yj⇔βj=1.

As for Cartesian product G◻H, V(G◻H)≅V(G)×V(G), (gi,hi)∼(gj,hj) if either

  • g1=g2 and h1∼h2 in H, w.r.t. (0,1)∈B.
  • h1=h2 and g1∼g2 in G, w.r.t. (1,0)∈B.

It is trivial to verify that:

  • ◻ is commutative.
  • ◻ is associative.

that is, the associativity and commutativity.

As for tensor product G×H, V(G×H)≅V(G)×V(H), (gi,hi)∼(gj,hj) if and only if (gi∼gj)∧(hi∼hj), w.r.t. B={(1,1)}.

The strong product G⊠H, w.r.t. B={0,1}2−{0,0}, etc.

The adjacency matrix (trivial proof by definition) is

A(NEPS({Gi}i=1n;B))=∑β∈B⊗i=1nA(Gi)βi.

Since (A⊗C)(B⊗D)=(AC)⊗(BD), the spectral outcome

∑β∈B(∏i=1nλiikβi)

where λiik is the k-th eigenvalue of Gi with corresponding eigenvalue xiik. Thus the eigen vector of A(NEPS({Gi}i=1n;B)) is

∑β∈B⊗i=1nxiik.
